benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/tags - Remove tags from invoice item

covered: DELETE Valid Deletion scenarios: TC01 (remove all tags), TC02 (remove specific tags), TC03 (optional headers), TC04 (no tags), TC05 (tagDef contains non-present IDs), TC06 (empty tagDef), TC07 (extra query params but only specified tags affected), TC08 (non-existent invoice item leads to 404), TC09 (invalid invoiceItemId format → 400), TC10 (missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy header → 400), TC11 (invalid/expired auth token → 401), TC12 (service unavailable → 503), TC13 (malformed tagDef values → 400), TC14 (very large tagDef → 204/413), TC15 (malicious headers → 400/422), TC16 (partial tagDef input → 400), TC17 (high concurrency), TC18 (special characters in comment), TC19 (dependent service unavailable → 204 or 207), TC20 (accessibility of docs and error messages)
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination handling for large datasets.
Caching Behavior: No tests testing caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control).
Rate Limiting: No dedicated tests for throttling or rate limiting.
Authorization edge case beyond missing header/invalid token (e.g., 403 for insufficient scope).
recommendations: Add tests for pagination behavior when listing/removing tags on large numbers of items (to exercise pagination logic if exposed).
Add tests validating caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) on DELETE responses where applicable.
Add explicit rate-limiting/throttling tests (e.g., many concurrent requests over a brief interval).
Add an explicit 403 scenario for insufficient permissions/scopes, and broaden header/auth edge cases (e.g., valid token but insufficient rights).
